The numbers are placed on the square‑spiral

\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
\cdots & 5&4&3&\cdots\\
\cdots & 6&1&2&\cdots\\
\cdots & 7&8&9&\cdots
\end{array}
\]

The centre (1) is at \((0,0)\); moving right gives 2, then up, left, down, etc.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 1.  Locate 2026  

For a point \((x,y)\) let  

\[
k=\max(|x|,|y|)
\]

be the “layer”.  
The largest number on layer \(k\) is  

\[
M_k=(2k+1)^2
\]

situated at \((k,-k)\).

For \(2026\) we have  

\[
\sqrt{2026}\approx 45.02,\qquad (2\cdot 23+1)^2 =45^2 =2025<2026<(2\cdot 24+1)^2=47^2=2209 .
\]

Hence \(k=23\).  
The maximum of this layer is \(M_{23}=47^{2}=2209\) at \((23,-23)\).  
Since 2025 is the previous layer’s maximum, the first number of the new layer (2026) is one step to the right:

\[
2026\ \text{at}\ (23,-22).
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
### 2.  Numbers of the eight neighbours  

The neighbours of \((23,-22)\) are the eight lattice points around it:

\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
(22,-23) & (23,-23) & (24,-23)\\[2mm]
(22,-22) &          & (24,-22)\\[2mm]
(22,-21) & (23,-21) & (24,-21)
\end{array}
\]

We need the value at each of these coordinates.

---

#### a)  Bottom‑edge of layer \(k=23\)  
For a point \((x,-k)\) (bottom edge)  

\[
n = M_k-(k-x).
\]

* \((22,-23) :\; n = 2209-(23-22)=2208\).

* \((23,-23)\) is the corner, \(n = 2209\).

* \((24,-23)\) belongs to the next layer (\(k=24\)).  
For the right edge of a layer \(k\) ( \(x=k,\,-k< y\le k\) )  

\[
n = M_k-\bigl(6k + (k-y)\bigr).
\]

With \(k=24,\; y=-23\):

\[
n = 2401-\bigl(6\cdot24+(24-(-23))\bigr)=2401-(144+47)=2210 .
\]

---

#### b)  Inside the previous layer (\(k=22\))

* \((22,-22)\) is the corner of layer 22: \(n=2025\).

* \((22,-21)\) lies on the right edge of layer 22 (\(x=22\)).  

\[
n = 2025-\bigl(6\cdot22+(22-(-21))\bigr)=2025-(132+43)=1850 .
\]

#### c)  Back to layer 23  

* \((24,-22)\) is on the right edge of layer 24:  

\[
n = 2401-\bigl(6\cdot24+(24-(-22))\bigr)=2401-(144+46)=2211 .
\]

* \((23,-21)\) is on the right edge of layer 23:

\[
n = 2209-\bigl(6\cdot23+(23-(-21))\bigr)=2209-(138+44)=2027 .
\]

* \((24,-21)\) (layer 24, right edge, \(y=-21\)):

\[
n = 2401-\bigl(144+(24-(-21))\bigr)=2401-(144+45)=2212 .
\]

---

### 3.  Sum of the eight neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{Sum}&=2208+2209+2210+2025+2211+1850+2027+2212 \\
&= 16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

--------------------------------------------------------------------
\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
----
